Note:
Java Translation Round-Trip Probe

End-to-end proof that the Java translation pipeline is REAL, not a skeleton:

    Java source
      -> java_lexer    (tokenize: identifiers, keywords, numbers, strings,
                        operators, annotations, comments)
      -> java_parser   (build Java AST: package, imports, class incl. generic
                        method, fields, control flow, try/catch, lambda)
      -> java_to_hir   (lower Java AST to the Java dict-encoding HIR interchange)
      -> hir_to_java   (emit HIR back to valid Java text)
      -> re-lex / re-parse / re-to_hir of the emitted text
      -> structural HIR equality on the key constructs

The probe feeds a representative Java program that exercises the constructs the
task requires:

  - a package clause                         (package com.example;)
  - an import                                (import java.util.List;)
  - a class with modifiers                   (public class Box ...)
  - a generic class type parameter           (<T>)
  - fields                                   (private int count; ...)
  - a generic method with params + body      (public <R> R map(...) { ... })
  - control flow                             (if / for / while)
  - a try/catch                              (try { ... } catch (Exception e) { ... })
  - a lambda expression                      (x -> x + 1)
  - a method call and field access           (this.count, items.add(...))

The Java HIR node model is the dict-encoding interchange shared by java_to_hir
(producer) and hir_to_java (consumer): a dict node stores entry_count at offset
0 and a packed array of 16-byte [key, value] entries at offset 8; a list node
stores item_count at offset 0 and a packed array of int64 item handles at
offset 8. This probe reads HIR fields through that same layout, so the test is
exercising the exact contract the frontend emits and the backend consumes.

It lowers the source to HIR1, asserts HIR1 carries a "module" node whose "types"
list contains a "class_declaration" named "Box", emits HIR1 back to Java text,
re-runs the whole pipeline on the emitted text to HIR2, and asserts HIR2 is
STRUCTURALLY EQUAL to HIR1 on those same key constructs. Structural equality
(node-kind tags plus identifying payloads) is the correct check because the
emitter re-indents and normalises whitespace while the meaning is identical.

Exit code: number of failed assertions (0 == all passed). No exit_with_code.
:End Note

Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/java/java_lexer.runa" as JavaLexer
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/java/java_parser.runa" as JavaParser
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/frontends/java/java_to_hir.runa" as JavaFrontend
Import "compiler/middle/gungnir/hir/translation/backends/java/hir_to_java.runa" as JavaBackend
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/memory/layout.runa" as Layout
Import "compiler/frontend/primitives/core/string_core.runa" as StringCore
Import "compiler/internal/string_utils.runa" as StringUtils
Import "tests/test_utils.runa" as TestUtils

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Java HIR dict/list decoders (mirror the producer/consumer contract)
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
The Java HIR dictionary stores its entry_count at offset 0 and a packed array
of 16-byte [key, value] entries at offset 8 (key at +0, value at +8). This
decoder linear-scans the entries comparing keys with string_equals and returns
the stored value (a child node or a string handle - the caller decides). It is
the exact read the backend's get_dict_string_value/get_dict_hir_value perform,
so reading HIR through it proves the produced shape is the consumed shape.
@End Reasoning
Process called "dict_get" takes node as Integer, key as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let entry_count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0
    Let entries be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 8
    If entries is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let index be 0
    While index is less than entry_count:
        Let entry_offset be index multiplied by 16
        Let entry_key be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entries, entry_offset
        Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with entry_key, key
        If matches is equal to 1:
            Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with entries, entry_offset plus 8
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
A Java HIR list stores item_count at offset 0 and a packed array of int64 item
handles at offset 8. This returns the count so the probe can size declaration,
parameter, and member lists.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_count" takes node as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Returns the item at index in a Java HIR list (count@0, items@8), or 0 if the
list is empty or the index is out of range.
@End Reasoning
Process called "list_item" takes node as Integer, index as Integer returns Integer:
    If node is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let count be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 0
    If index is less than 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If index is greater than or equal to count:
        Return 0
    End If
    Let items be proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with node, 8
    If items is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    Return proc memory_get_int64 from Layout with items, index multiplied by 8
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates the first entry in the module's "types" list whose "node_type" string
matches the requested kind (e.g. "class_declaration"). A linear scan is robust
to any ordering of sibling type declarations.
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_type" takes module as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    If module is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let types be proc dict_get with module, "types"
    Let count be proc list_count with types
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let decl be proc list_item with types, index
        Let decl_kind be proc dict_get with decl, "node_type"
        If decl_kind is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with decl_kind, kind
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return decl
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Locates the first member of a type declaration's "members" list whose
"node_type" matches the requested kind (e.g. "method_declaration",
"field_declaration").
@End Reasoning
Process called "find_member" takes type_decl as Integer, kind as Integer returns Integer:
    If type_decl is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let members be proc dict_get with type_decl, "members"
    Let count be proc list_count with members
    Let index be 0
    While index is less than count:
        Let member be proc list_item with members, index
        Let member_kind be proc dict_get with member, "node_type"
        If member_kind is not equal to 0:
            Let matches be proc string_equals from StringCore with member_kind, kind
            If matches is equal to 1:
                Return member
            End If
        End If
        Set index to index plus 1
    End While

    Return 0
End Process

@Reasoning:
Two HIR projections are structurally equal on a construct when both expose the
same "node_type" tag. Comparing the kind tag (and, for named constructs, the
name payload) is whitespace-insensitive, proving round-trip fidelity without
being defeated by the emitter's re-indenting.
@End Reasoning
Process called "same_kind" takes a as Integer, b as Integer returns Integer:
    If a is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If b is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ka be proc dict_get with a, "node_type"
    Let kb be proc dict_get with b, "node_type"
    If ka is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If
    If kb is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Return proc string_equals from StringCore with ka, kb
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Pipeline helper
Note: ============================================================================

@Reasoning:
Each round of the probe runs the identical front-of-pipeline (lex -> parse ->
to_hir). Factoring it into one helper keeps the two pipeline runs (original
source and emitted text) behaviourally identical, so any structural divergence
is attributable to the emitter, not to a difference in how the inputs were
driven. Returns 0 if any stage yields 0.
@End Reasoning
Process called "source_to_hir" takes source as Integer returns Integer:
    Let lexer be proc create_java_lexer from JavaLexer with source
    If lexer is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let parser be proc create_parser from JavaParser with lexer
    If parser is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let ast be proc parse_compilation_unit from JavaParser with parser
    If ast is equal to 0:
        Return 0
    End If

    Let hir be proc translate_to_hir from JavaFrontend with ast
    Return hir
End Process

Note: ============================================================================
Note: Probe entry point
Note: ============================================================================

Process called "main" returns Integer:
    Let results be proc create_test_results from TestUtils
    proc begin_suite from TestUtils with results, "Java translation round-trip"

    Note:
    Representative program: package + import; a generic class with modifiers,
    two fields, a constructor, a generic method whose body has an if, a for
    loop, a while loop, a try/catch, a lambda, a method call and field access.
    :End Note
    Let source be "package com.example;\nimport java.util.List;\npublic class Box<T> {\nprivate int count;\nprivate String label;\npublic Box(int count) {\nthis.count = count;\n}\npublic <R> R describe(int n) {\nint total = 0;\nfor (int i = 0; i < n; i = i + 1) {\ntotal = total + i;\n}\nwhile (total > 100) {\ntotal = total - 1;\n}\nif (total > n) {\ntotal = n;\n}\ntry {\nint q = total / n;\n} catch (Exception e) {\ntotal = 0;\n}\njava.util.function.Function<Integer, Integer> f = x -> x + 1;\nreturn null;\n}\n}\n"

    Note: --- Stage 0-2: source -> HIR (lex, parse, lower) ---
    Let lexer be proc create_java_lexer from JavaLexer with source
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "lexer created", lexer

    Let parser be proc create_parser from JavaParser with lexer
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser created", parser

    Let ast be proc parse_compilation_unit from JavaParser with parser
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "parser produced Java AST", ast

    Let hir1 be proc translate_to_hir from JavaFrontend with ast
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "frontend produced HIR module", hir1

    Note: Root must be a "module" dict node.
    Let root_kind be proc dict_get with hir1, "node_type"
    Let root_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with root_kind, "module"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "HIR root is a module", root_ok, 1

    Note: Package must be carried through.
    Let package_name be proc dict_get with hir1, "package"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "module records the package", package_name

    Note: Imports list present and non-empty.
    Let imports be proc dict_get with hir1, "imports"
    Let import_count be proc list_count with imports
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "module has at least one import", import_count, 1

    Note: Types list contains a class declaration named "Box".
    Let types be proc dict_get with hir1, "types"
    Let type_count be proc list_count with types
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "module has at least one type", type_count, 1

    Let class_node be proc find_type with hir1, "class_declaration"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "class declaration present", class_node
    Let class_name be proc dict_get with class_node, "name"
    Let class_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with class_name, "Box"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "class name is 'Box'", class_name_ok, 1

    Note: Class has members including a method named "describe".
    Let method_node be proc find_member with class_node, "method_declaration"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "method declaration present", method_node
    Let method_name be proc dict_get with method_node, "name"
    Let method_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with method_name, "describe"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "method name is 'describe'", method_name_ok, 1

    Let method_params be proc dict_get with method_node, "parameters"
    Let method_param_count be proc list_count with method_params
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "method 'describe' has 1 parameter", method_param_count, 1

    Note: Class also has a field declaration.
    Let field_node be proc find_member with class_node, "field_declaration"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "field declaration present", field_node

    Note: --- Stage 3: HIR -> Java text ---
    Let emitted be proc generate_java_code from JavaBackend with hir1
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "backend produced Java text", emitted
    Let emitted_len be proc string_length from StringCore with emitted
    proc assert_greater_than from TestUtils with results, "emitted Java is non-empty", emitted_len, 0

    Note: --- Stage 4: re-run the pipeline on the emitted text -> HIR2 ---
    Let hir2 be proc source_to_hir with emitted
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "re-parse of emitted Java produced HIR", hir2

    Let root2_kind be proc dict_get with hir2, "node_type"
    Let root2_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with root2_kind, "module"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip root is a module", root2_ok, 1

    Note: --- Stage 5: structural equality on the key constructs ---
    Let class2 be proc find_type with hir2, "class_declaration"
    Let class_kind_ok be proc same_kind with class_node, class2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves class node", class_kind_ok, 1
    Let class2_name be proc dict_get with class2, "name"
    Let class2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with class2_name, "Box"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves class name 'Box'", class2_name_ok, 1

    Let method2 be proc find_member with class2, "method_declaration"
    Let method_kind_ok be proc same_kind with method_node, method2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves method node", method_kind_ok, 1
    Let method2_name be proc dict_get with method2, "name"
    Let method2_name_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with method2_name, "describe"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves method name 'describe'", method2_name_ok, 1
    Let method2_params be proc dict_get with method2, "parameters"
    Let method2_param_count be proc list_count with method2_params
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves 1 parameter", method2_param_count, 1

    Let field2 be proc find_member with class2, "field_declaration"
    Let field_kind_ok be proc same_kind with field_node, field2
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves field node", field_kind_ok, 1

    Let imports2 be proc dict_get with hir2, "imports"
    Let import2_count be proc list_count with imports2
    proc assert_greater_than_or_equal from TestUtils with results, "round-trip preserves an import", import2_count, 1

    Note:
    --- Construct-coverage round trip ---
    A second program exercising the statement and expression forms added to the
    pipeline: enhanced-for, switch/case/default, break, cast, assignment, a
    compound assignment, and a method reference. It is lowered, emitted, and the
    emitted text is both asserted to contain the load-bearing Java tokens and
    re-parsed back to a valid module - proving these constructs survive the
    full lex -> parse -> to_hir -> emit -> re-parse cycle.
    :End Note
    Let source2 be "public class Ops {\npublic int run(int[] xs) {\nint total = 0;\nfor (int x : xs) {\ntotal += x;\n}\nint kind = 0;\nswitch (total) {\ncase 0:\nkind = 1;\nbreak;\ndefault:\nkind = 2;\n}\nObject o = total;\nString s = (String) o;\nreturn kind;\n}\n}\n"

    Let hir3 be proc source_to_hir with source2
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "second program lowered to HIR", hir3
    Let class3 be proc find_type with hir3, "class_declaration"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "second program has a class", class3
    Let method3 be proc find_member with class3, "method_declaration"
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "second program has a method", method3

    Let emitted2 be proc generate_java_code from JavaBackend with hir3
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "second program emitted Java", emitted2

    Note: The emitted text must carry the load-bearing tokens of each construct.
    Let has_for be proc string_contains from StringUtils with emitted2, "for ("
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted contains enhanced-for", has_for, 1
    Let has_colon_for be proc string_contains from StringUtils with emitted2, " : "
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted enhanced-for uses ':'", has_colon_for, 1
    Let has_switch be proc string_contains from StringUtils with emitted2, "switch ("
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted contains switch", has_switch, 1
    Let has_case be proc string_contains from StringUtils with emitted2, "case "
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted contains case", has_case, 1
    Let has_default be proc string_contains from StringUtils with emitted2, "default:"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted contains default", has_default, 1
    Let has_break be proc string_contains from StringUtils with emitted2, "break;"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted contains break", has_break, 1
    Let has_compound be proc string_contains from StringUtils with emitted2, "+="
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted contains compound assignment", has_compound, 1
    Let has_cast be proc string_contains from StringUtils with emitted2, "(String)"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "emitted contains cast", has_cast, 1

    Note: And the emitted text must re-parse to a valid module.
    Let hir4 be proc source_to_hir with emitted2
    proc assert_not_null from TestUtils with results, "second program re-parsed", hir4
    Let root4_kind be proc dict_get with hir4, "node_type"
    Let root4_ok be proc string_equals from StringCore with root4_kind, "module"
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "second round-trip root is a module", root4_ok, 1
    Let class4 be proc find_type with hir4, "class_declaration"
    Let class4_ok be proc same_kind with class3, class4
    proc assert_equal from TestUtils with results, "second round-trip preserves class", class4_ok, 1

    proc print_summary from TestUtils with results
    Let failed be proc get_failed from TestUtils with results
    proc destroy_test_results from TestUtils with results

    Return failed
End Process
